28/10/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- During a meeting Wednesday (28 October) with the leadership of the ruling New Democracy (ND) party, Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis reiterated that he and the government are determined to fight corruption and introduce transparency in public administration. 
As for ND's recent initiatives to investigate corruption and mismanagement scandals linked to the former administration, Karamanlis said they were "not interested in a witch hunt". 
He added that there should be rules -- applicable to all -- in the country. 
(ANA - 28/10/04)
